The paper deals with cost sharing problems in cooperative games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves statistical methods for deriving cost functions from data, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms for computing the core and Shapley value, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
